Brawl Starsâ history began in 2017 when Supercell introduced the game. In June 2017, it entered a closed beta phase in Canada for iOS users, where players could join by invitation only. During this period, the game saw continuous updates with new characters, game modes, and maps based on player feedback.
In June 2018, the Android version of Brawl Stars also entered beta in Canada, allowing a broader audience to test the game. In November 2018, Supercell announced that Brawl Stars would be globally released in December. On December 12, 2018, Brawl Stars was officially launched worldwide on both iOS and Android platforms, quickly gaining immense popularity.

From 2019 onward, Brawl Stars received regular updates and events, with Supercell adding new characters (Brawlers), game modes, and maps to keep the game fresh and engaging. The game has maintained its popularity and continues to be enjoyed by millions of players around the world.
